Defendant Anibal B Cosme in court with Attorney Heather L. Johnson.  Defendant Anibal B Cosme in custody.  Stephan Eduard Nolten appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for Competency hearing.  Competency Hearing proceeded.  State does not challenge Dr. Matthew Seipel report.  Defense does challenge Dr.Matthew Seipel report.  Court qualified Dr.Matthew Seipel to testify as an expert.  Sworn for the State:  Dr.  Seipel.  Testimony closed.  Arguments heard.  The allowed the  defendant Anibal Cosme made a Statement.
After review of all evidence, report of Dr.  Seipel, and testimony of Dr. Seipel, Court finds defendant incompetent to proceed at this time but is likely to become competent.  Court found the defendant is not competent to refuse psychotropic medication or treatment due to mental illness because the defendant is incapable of expressing an understanding of the advantages and disadvantages of accepting psychotropic medication or treatment.  Court ordered defendant commitment for treatment for incompetency.  Order signed and filed.  The sheriff shall arrange for transportation of the defendant to the treatment facility.  The defendant shall be given 51 days of credit for precommitment incarceration.  The Department of Health and Family Services is authorized to administer psychotropic medication or treatment to the defendant, and shall observe appropriate medical standards.  Court ordered case adjourned for return on doctor's report on 6/28/2022 at 9:00am  in Branch 45.
